midwifery manual,

00:22:45.370 --> 00:22:47.160
advised that women
who were, quote,

00:22:47.160 --> 00:22:49.850
"hindered very much for a want
of desire to be acquainted with

00:22:49.850 --> 00:22:52.630
Venus"-- the language of how
they describe sexual pleasure

00:22:52.630 --> 00:22:55.120
is just amazing
throughout the whole era--

00:22:55.120 --> 00:22:58.930
"should take heating herbs such
as gelengal, rocket, pepper,

00:22:58.930 --> 00:23:00.980
ginger, and cinnamon."

00:23:00.980 --> 00:23:03.094
And it was some of those
spices in chocolate,

00:23:03.094 --> 00:23:05.260
and it was that heating
effect in the chocolate that

00:23:05.260 --> 00:23:07.730
was thought to be
aphrodisiac as well.

00:23:07.730 --> 00:23:09.590
While another Englishman,
Philip Barrow,

00:23:09.590 --> 00:23:11.830
writing in the
16th century stated

00:23:11.830 --> 00:23:13.260
that "frigid men
and women should

00:23:13.260 --> 00:23:16.210
eat meats that do heat and
engender good humors, as is

00:23:16.210 --> 00:23:19.420
the flesh of hens, capons,
partridges, pheasants,

00:23:19.420 --> 00:23:22.520
young doves, birds of the
mountain, especially sparrows,

00:23:22.520 --> 00:23:24.630
cockstones, and suchlike."

00:23:24.630 --> 00:23:26.680
So clearly you're not
lacking for options.

00:23:26.680 --> 00:23:29.820
There's quite a few
things you can choose.

00:23:29.820 --> 00:23:33.310
The most famous of all of the
hot foods and heating herbs,

00:23:33.310 --> 00:23:36.510
though, was the Spanish
fly, Contharides.

00:23:36.510 --> 00:23:38.430
And this small,
iridescent beetle

00:23:38.430 --> 00:23:40.910
was very rarely recommended
by medical writers.

00:23:40.910 --> 00:23:43.110
It's incredibly dangerous.

00:23:43.110 --> 00:23:44.850
And it's incredibly
dangerous still.

00:23:44.850 --> 00:23:49.240
And I'm not sure I'm-- well,
people often end up on my blog,

00:23:49.240 --> 00:23:51.680
I can see what they've been
searching for, and a lot

00:23:51.680 --> 00:23:53.850
of people are searching
for Contharides and whether

00:23:53.850 --> 00:23:54.510
they're dangerous.

00:23:54.510 --> 00:23:56.593
And I just want a big
banner on my blog that says,

00:23:56.593 --> 00:23:58.760
yes, don't use them.

00:23:58.760 --> 00:24:02.182
They're known to blister
and burn the skin.

00:24:02.182 --> 00:24:04.140
And that's both if they're
applied to the skin,

00:24:04.140 --> 00:24:05.560
or if they're
consumed internally,

00:24:05.560 --> 00:24:08.190
they'll blister and
burn internally.

00:24:08.190 --> 00:24:11.220
But they do create
this warming sensation.

00:24:11.220 --> 00:24:13.925
So anything that's hot
under the humoral model

00:24:13.925 --> 00:24:16.060
or creates that sensation
of warmth when you eat it

00:24:16.060 --> 00:24:18.170
is really good as
a heating herb.

00:24:18.170 --> 00:24:22.340
And Contharides are
probably the most potent.

00:24:22.340 --> 00:24:25.260
So given how dangerous
it was, medical writers

00:24:25.260 --> 00:24:27.240
didn't really like
to recommend it.

00:24:27.240 --> 00:24:30.720
And in fact, they spent a lot
of time trying to warn people

00:24:30.720 --> 00:24:32.640
about the side effects.

00:24:32.640 --> 00:24:35.500
And Jane Sharp, who was the
first woman and Englishwoman

00:24:35.500 --> 00:24:38.640
to ever write a midwifery
text and publish it in England

00:24:38.640 --> 00:24:41.930
writes of Contharides,
or Spanish fly.

00:24:41.930 --> 00:24:43.480
She warns people
"not to take them

00:24:43.480 --> 00:24:45.000
to stimulate an
erection, because it

00:24:45.000 --> 00:24:47.760
could result in a priapism,
or a continual standing

00:24:47.760 --> 00:24:48.955
of the yard."

00:24:48.955 --> 00:24:51.330
Yard is one of their term--
I don't need to explain that,

00:24:51.330 --> 00:24:52.240
do I?

00:24:52.240 --> 00:24:53.340
[LAUGHTER]

00:24:53.340 --> 00:24:55.240
We don't think it's
based on length, though.

00:24:55.240 --> 00:24:56.860
We're still trying
to figure that out.

00:24:56.860 --> 00:24:59.060
So priapism, or continual
standing of the yard,

00:24:59.060 --> 00:25:01.100
which she goes on to
say is more of a problem

00:25:01.100 --> 00:25:02.750
than if it never stands at all.

00:25:02.750 --> 00:25:03.880
And she's not wrong.

00:25:03.880 --> 00:25:04.760
[LAUGHTER]

00:25:04.760 --> 00:25:08.280
Other writers tend towards
quite gruesome tales.

00:25:08.280 --> 00:25:10.090
They like to recite
a nice little story

00:25:10.090 --> 00:25:11.590
to try and put people off.

00:25:11.590 --> 00:25:13.810
And the Swiss physician
Theophile Bonet,

00:25:13.810 --> 00:25:16.690
who is working in Geneva,
records in his medical texts

00:25:16.690 --> 00:25:19.730
that, "I've known several among
the rest, two noblemen who

00:25:19.730 --> 00:25:21.755
used Contharides,
the one to gratify

00:25:21.755 --> 00:25:24.260
his whore, the other,
his new married wife,

00:25:24.260 --> 00:25:26.470
but wholly with ill
success, for the first

00:25:26.470 --> 00:25:28.990
fell into a most dangerous
pissing of blood, of which he

00:25:28.990 --> 00:25:30.656
was cured with great difficulty.

00:25:30.656 --> 00:25:32.780
And the other, the second
day after he was married,

00:25:32.780 --> 00:25:34.700
died of an apoplexy,"
which is what we would

00:25:34.700 --> 00:25:36.910
now term a stroke.

00:25:36.910 --> 00:25:39.360
So heating aphrodisiacs
are very popular

00:25:39.360 --> 00:25:42.960
throughout the entire era,
but they're quite dangerous,

00:25:42.960 --> 00:25:45.360
particularly the Spanish fly.

00:25:45.360 --> 00:25:48.600
Now, many of the foods that
were thought to be warming also

00:25:48.600 --> 00:25:53.040
were thought to fit in our next
category, which is nourishing

00:25:53.040 --> 00:25:56.460
foods and seed provokers.

00:25:56.460 --> 00:25:58.490
Any food that
nourished the body was

00:25:58.490 --> 00:26:00.366
thought to be good
as an aphrodisiac

00:26:00.366 --> 00:26:01.990
because it fundamentally
meant that you

00:26:01.990 --> 00:26:04.107
were producing more seed.

00:26:04.107 --> 00:26:06.190
For early modern men and
women, you eat your food,

00:26:06.190 --> 00:26:09.370
it sits in the stomach,
gets converted into blood,

00:26:09.370 --> 00:26:12.737
blood circulates around the
body, ends up in the testicles,

00:26:12.737 --> 00:26:14.820
or depending on which text
you read, the prostate,

00:26:14.820 --> 00:26:17.350
because some people think
the prostate is doing this,

00:26:17.350 --> 00:26:21.470
where it's-- they term it
concocted or elaborated

00:26:21.470 --> 00:26:23.250
and turned into seed.

00:26:23.250 --> 00:26:26.950
And so blood that was
food becomes seed.

00:26:26.950 --> 00:26:29.260
And so anything you
eat that's nourishing

00:26:29.260 --> 00:26:31.590
is producing more
seed in your body.

00:26:31.590 --> 00:26:33.600
And seed is really
important because it's

00:26:33.600 --> 00:26:35.450
thought to be stimulating.

00:26:35.450 --> 00:26:37.690
So as it passes through
all the little passageways

00:26:37.690 --> 00:26:41.310
of the reproductive organs,
it stimulates sexual pleasure.

00:26:41.310 --> 00:26:43.640
And this is where you get
that complex desire-pleasure

00:26:43.640 --> 00:26:45.860
crossover, because
the production of seed

00:26:45.860 --> 00:26:49.090
is stimulated by desire,
which creates pleasure,

00:26:49.090 --> 00:26:51.260
but the pleasure also
stimulates the desire, which

00:26:51.260 --> 00:26:52.620
creates the seed production.

00:26:52.620 --> 00:26:54.560
And I think they
get as confused as I

00:26:54.560 --> 00:26:57.980
do when they were writing them.

00:26:57.980 --> 00:27:02.530
So anything that helps
nourish you produces seed.

00:27:02.530 --> 00:27:06.390
And better quality seed
gives more titillation.

00:27:06.390 --> 00:27:08.470
But importantly,
it's also more likely

00:27:08.470 --> 00:27:10.390
to result in a
conception, so again,

00:27:10.390 --> 00:27:13.280
this link between
sex and reproduction.

00:27:13.280 --> 00:27:16.280
So if we look back at
Felix Plater's 1662 book,

00:27:16.280 --> 00:27:18.160
he loves this category.

00:27:18.160 --> 00:27:20.520
He goes nuts and lists
huge amounts of things.

00:27:20.520 --> 00:27:22.840
And so he says,
"To correct a want

00:27:22.840 --> 00:27:27.750
of copulation in particular,
we give things that cause seed.

00:27:27.750 --> 00:27:30.970
And this, as is said, by
its plenty and sharpness

00:27:30.970 --> 00:27:34.830
stirs up desire to the act and
disposes the members for it.

00:27:34.830 --> 00:27:36.410
These are such as
cause much blood,

00:27:36.410 --> 00:27:38.820
which is the matter of
which seed is made."

00:27:38.820 --> 00:27:40.760
Some some suggestions
that he offered

00:27:40.760 --> 00:27:44.800
were the "brain's stones," which
is their word for testicles,

00:27:44.800 --> 00:27:49.200
and flesh of crawfish, crabs,
lobsters, oysters, cuttlefish,

00:27:49.200 --> 00:27:53.100
[INAUDIBLE], cocks, quails,
sparrows, and foxes, as well as

00:27:53.100 --> 00:27:57.140
milk, eggs, chestnuts, parsnips,
almonds, pine nuts, pistachios,

00:27:57.140 --> 00:28:01.370
artichokes, rapeseed, beans,
peas, rice, and barley.

00:28:01.370 --> 00:28:04.680
So you were definitely not going
to not find an aphrodisiac.

00:28:04.680 --> 00:28:07.710
There's always something
you can turn to.

00:28:07.710 --> 00:28:10.950
Now, a very similar category
to these are seed provokers.

00:28:10.950 --> 00:28:13.960
And when I was writing the book
and doing the research for it.

00:28:13.960 --> 00:28:15.960
I kept coming across
these two kind

00:28:15.960 --> 00:28:19.070
of interchangeable terms,
nourishing foods and seed

00:28:19.070 --> 00:28:19.610
provokers.

00:28:19.610 --> 00:28:22.100
And in the 18th century, they
even get called spermatics,

00:28:22.100 --> 00:28:24.700
which I quite like as a term.

00:28:24.700 --> 00:28:27.274
But I think, depending
on where you're reading,

00:28:27.274 --> 00:28:29.440
these are either the same
thing, or they're actually

00:28:29.440 --> 00:28:30.273
something different.

00:28:30.273 --> 00:28:32.770
And a seed provoker is
something that prompts the body

00:28:32.770 --> 00:28:36.000
to make seed out of nourishment
that's already there as opposed

00:28:36.000 --> 00:28:38.650
to just providing more
of the base material.

00:28:38.650 --> 00:28:40.687
And Felix Plater's is
one of the text where

00:28:40.687 --> 00:28:42.520
you can see this
distinction, because having

00:28:42.520 --> 00:28:45.020
given that huge, long
list of nourishing foods,

00:28:45.020 --> 00:28:49.510
he goes on to say that you could
also take these seed provokers.

00:28:49.510 --> 00:28:52.520
And he says that these are
onions, leeks, mushrooms,

00:28:52.520 --> 00:28:55.025
rocket, colewart, which
is a type of brassica,

00:28:55.025 --> 00:28:57.430
a bit like kale, and asparagus.

00:28:57.430 --> 00:29:01.440
And so he's quite clear
to separate the two out.

00:29:01.440 --> 00:29:04.650
Now, I've said seed
was titillating.

00:29:04.650 --> 00:29:06.280
There is a reason for that.

00:29:06.280 --> 00:29:08.230
The reason why
seed is titillating

00:29:08.230 --> 00:29:10.750
is because of its salt content.

00:29:10.750 --> 00:29:14.150
They believe that seed is salty.

00:29:14.150 --> 00:29:17.390
And so another category
of aphrodisiacs

00:29:17.390 --> 00:29:21.080
are salty or slightly
salty, brackish foods,

00:29:21.080 --> 00:29:23.290
because they augment
the quality of seed

00:29:23.290 --> 00:29:25.080
that makes it titillating.

00:29:25.080 --> 00:29:28.370
And one medical
writer is [INAUDIBLE].

00:29:28.370 --> 00:29:30.630
He explains in the 17th
century that "salt,

00:29:30.630 --> 00:29:32.680
by reason of its
heat and acrimony,

00:29:32.680 --> 00:29:34.690
provokes to lust those
that used to eat it

00:29:34.690 --> 00:29:36.055
in any great quantity.

00:29:36.055 --> 00:29:38.180
And it was for this cause
that the Egyptian priests

00:29:38.180 --> 00:29:40.740
would want to abstain from
all manner of salt meats,

00:29:40.740 --> 00:29:42.990
having found by experience
that salt does cause

00:29:42.990 --> 00:29:45.950
a kind of itching or
tickling in the parts that

00:29:45.950 --> 00:29:48.910
serve for generation."

00:29:48.910 --> 00:29:54.460
And this is quite a nice
anecdote that he includes.

00:29:54.460 --> 00:29:56.580
It sounds quite sophisticated.

00:29:56.580 --> 00:29:58.830
Another text I read was
slightly less sophisticated

00:29:58.830 --> 00:30:00.840
and said it was
evident that salt

00:30:00.840 --> 00:30:02.770
was an aphrodisiac
because mice on ships are

00:30:02.770 --> 00:30:04.952
want to breed quite excessively.

00:30:04.952 --> 00:30:07.410
And even if you have one mouse,
by the end of your journey,

00:30:07.410 --> 00:30:08.910
you'll have lots,
and that's clearly

00:30:08.910 --> 00:30:12.120
the fault of licking
salt from off the ship.

00:30:12.120 --> 00:30:15.370
Theophile Bonet, our Swiss
physician we met earlier

00:30:15.370 --> 00:30:17.940
liked to link it more to Venus.

00:30:17.940 --> 00:30:21.070
And he said that "saline
and acrimonious things

00:30:21.070 --> 00:30:23.730
were aphrodisiacs
because, as Venus

00:30:23.730 --> 00:30:26.680
is said to be born of
salt sea, so saline things

00:30:26.680 --> 00:30:28.150
you know to be stimulate."

00:30:28.150 --> 00:30:31.090
And he goes so far as to say
that the word "salacious" must

00:30:31.090 --> 00:30:33.430
all be connected into this
because of that "sal,"

00:30:33.430 --> 00:30:38.860
"salaciois," "saline" all
comes connected to Venus.

00:30:38.860 --> 00:30:41.110
What I found really interesting
while writing the book

00:30:41.110 --> 00:30:44.530
is that lots and lots of medical
texts in the 17th country

00:30:44.530 --> 00:30:45.695
just kind of cut and paste.

00:30:45.695 --> 00:30:48.160
They're huge fans of plagiarism.

00:30:48.160 --> 00:30:51.522
They will republish and reprint
and steal from each other

00:30:51.522 --> 00:30:52.480
over and over and over.

00:30:52.480 --> 00:30:55.310
So change can be
quite slow to identify

00:30:55.310 --> 00:30:59.019
and slow to make its way
through these kinds of texts.

00:30:59.019 --> 00:31:00.560
But throughout the
17th century, they

00:31:00.560 --> 00:31:02.390
are questioning
their aphrodisiacs.

00:31:02.390 --> 00:31:03.770
They're questioning what works.

00:31:03.770 --> 00:31:06.440
And poor saline,
salty foods are one

00:31:06.440 --> 00:31:09.480
of the first kind of casualties
of this reexamination.

00:31:09.480 --> 00:31:12.972
And John Martin, who wrote about
pleasure-- we saw him earlier--

00:31:12.972 --> 00:31:14.430
he writes in the
early 18th century

00:31:14.430 --> 00:31:16.096
that there's no way
that these can work,

00:31:16.096 --> 00:31:18.740
because there's not
enough salt in seed

00:31:18.740 --> 00:31:19.947
for it to be stimulating.

00:31:19.947 --> 00:31:22.030
And I think his word choice
is really interesting,

00:31:22.030 --> 00:31:25.220
because he's not outright
saying salt isn't aphrodisiac,

00:31:25.220 --> 00:31:27.412
just that there's not enough
there, which to my mind

00:31:27.412 --> 00:31:28.870
would mean a reader
would just say,

00:31:28.870 --> 00:31:31.860
oh, well I'll eat lots more
of it and then it will work.

00:31:31.860 --> 00:31:33.420
But he's trying to
distance himself

00:31:33.420 --> 00:31:38.800
from that kind of understanding.

00:31:38.800 --> 00:31:41.460
Others are a bit more
argumentative and forceful.

00:31:41.460 --> 00:31:43.140
And so say salty
foods stop being

00:31:43.140 --> 00:31:45.350
described as an
aphrodisiac fairly early

00:31:45.350 --> 00:31:47.700
in the 18th century.

00:31:47.700 --> 00:31:50.180
So, so far, hopefully
you've picked up

00:31:50.180 --> 00:31:53.030
on this, all of these foods
work for both men and women.

00:31:53.030 --> 00:31:54.810
And that in part is
because of that idea

00:31:54.810 --> 00:31:56.520
that men and women's
bodies are very similar.

00:31:56.520 --> 00:31:57.800
They do function
in different ways,

00:31:57.800 --> 00:31:59.020
but they're quite similar.

00:31:59.020 --> 00:32:02.390
But there was one aphrodisiac
that was solely for the men's

00:32:02.390 --> 00:32:03.870
bodies, solely for men.

00:32:03.870 --> 00:32:06.060
And this is normally my
most popular category

00:32:06.060 --> 00:32:08.230
of aphrodisiacs.

00:32:08.230 --> 00:32:10.570
They were things that
cause flatulence,

00:32:10.570 --> 00:32:13.260
so flatulence foods
come to be known

00:32:13.260 --> 00:32:15.570
as windy meats in
the 17th century

00:32:15.570 --> 00:32:17.270
and in the early modern era.

00:32:17.270 --> 00:32:20.030
And anything that releases
wind into the body,

00:32:20.030 --> 00:32:23.730
into the reproductive organs,
is supposed to be good for men.

00:32:23.730 --> 00:32:26.510
The reason it's good for men
is because the way anatomy

00:32:26.510 --> 00:32:29.405
understands the male body at
the very beginning of the era

00:32:29.405 --> 00:32:31.460
is they think that
an erection functions

00:32:31.460 --> 00:32:34.870
through blood, imagination,
muscles, pressure, seed,

00:32:34.870 --> 00:32:36.050
and wind.

00:32:36.050 --> 00:32:39.980
And this is my second-favorite
quote from the book.

00:32:39.980 --> 00:32:43.070
Helkiah Crooke, an Englishman,
writes of the male member

00:32:43.070 --> 00:32:46.010
that it was, quote, "a gut
filled with wind, presently

00:32:46.010 --> 00:32:48.910
swelling and grown hard,"
so not a very sophisticated

00:32:48.910 --> 00:32:50.560
understanding of the male body.

00:32:50.560 --> 00:32:53.770
And windy meats are
really bad for women.

00:32:53.770 --> 00:32:57.950
Wind collecting in the womb is
a disorder called the dropsy.

00:32:57.950 --> 00:33:00.200
It's very bad, but there are
some very amusing stories

00:33:00.200 --> 00:33:02.180
about when that wind
is released from women.

00:33:02.180 --> 00:33:04.470
Medical writers like
to write about that.

00:33:04.470 --> 00:33:06.920
But dropsy actually
causes barrenness,

00:33:06.920 --> 00:33:09.690
so it's a bad thing for
women, but it's good for men.

00:33:09.690 --> 00:33:11.770
Now, the reason this
is so good for men

00:33:11.770 --> 00:33:14.660
is because it
facilitates an erection.

00:33:14.660 --> 00:33:16.700
We might think that's
purely mechanical.

00:33:16.700 --> 00:33:18.640
So are they really
aphrodisiacs if it's just

00:33:18.640 --> 00:33:20.000
aiding the mechanics?

00:33:20.000 --> 00:33:24.020
But by enhancing and
lengthening the amount of time

00:33:24.020 --> 00:33:26.005
a man can sustain
an erection for,

00:33:26.005 --> 00:33:27.380
what they believe
is happening is

00:33:27.380 --> 00:33:30.520
you're giving more time for
friction, which causes more

00:33:30.520 --> 00:33:34.110
heat, but you're also giving
more time for that woman's

00:33:34.110 --> 00:33:37.430
colder body to get to a
point where she will orgasm.

00:33:37.430 --> 00:33:39.330
And so there is more
chance of those two

00:33:39.330 --> 00:33:42.660
seeds meeting at the
same moment in the womb

00:33:42.660 --> 00:33:44.160
and forming a fetus.

00:33:44.160 --> 00:33:48.890
So again, it's kind of pleasure,
but in a really off mechanical,

00:33:48.890 --> 00:33:51.180
mechanistic kind of way.

00:33:51.180 --> 00:33:53.140
So the flatulent
category, probably not

00:33:53.140 --> 00:33:58.110
a surprise to anyone, includes
beans, peas, and chickpeas.

00:33:58.110 --> 00:34:00.360
And Philip Barrow,
who we met earlier,

00:34:00.360 --> 00:34:02.660
argued that when a man
cannot fulfill his duties,

00:34:02.660 --> 00:34:05.910
which I think is a very
interesting phrase, quote,

00:34:05.910 --> 00:34:09.210
"windy meats are good for him,
as be chick peas and beans,

00:34:09.210 --> 00:34:12.630
scallions, leeks, the root and
seed of parsnips, pine nuts,

00:34:12.630 --> 00:34:15.170
sweet almonds, and
other such like."

00:34:15.170 --> 00:34:17.679
Again, anything that's
similar will work.

00:34:17.679 --> 00:34:20.540
Another author claimed
a similarly long list

00:34:20.540 --> 00:34:23.110
of foods as windy
aphrodisiacs, including

00:34:23.110 --> 00:34:26.360
pine nuts, pistachios, small
nuts, chives, artichokes,

00:34:26.360 --> 00:34:30.989
colewarts, rapes, carrots,
parsnips, green ginger, eryngo,

00:34:30.989 --> 00:34:34.969
which is a plant that grows
in coastal areas in England,

00:34:34.969 --> 00:34:38.070
satyrion, which we're going to
see in a minute, onions, water

00:34:38.070 --> 00:34:40.570
nuts, rockets, et
cetera, oysters,

00:34:40.570 --> 00:34:44.290
also chestnuts, chickpeas,
and all such like meats.

00:34:44.290 --> 00:34:46.690
And I think you can
see here this repeated

00:34:46.690 --> 00:34:48.550
phrase of "and suchlike."

00:34:48.550 --> 00:34:50.330
And so they're very
open to the concept

00:34:50.330 --> 00:34:52.671
that if you haven't got
exactly what's on my list,

00:34:52.671 --> 00:34:54.420
anything you've got
that's kind of similar

00:34:54.420 --> 00:34:57.770
is probably going to work, which
is very important when you're

00:34:57.770 --> 00:35:01.410
talking about quite
a varied wealth

00:35:01.410 --> 00:35:04.110
dynamic across the country.

00:35:04.110 --> 00:35:07.870
As with salty foods, windy
meats, unfortunately-- I

00:35:07.870 --> 00:35:11.350
think it's a real shame-- fall
foul of the reinterpretation

00:35:11.350 --> 00:35:13.540
and reinvestigation
of aphrodisiacs,

00:35:13.540 --> 00:35:15.430
and increasingly across
the 17th century,

00:35:15.430 --> 00:35:18.000
anatomists point out that
the penis is a lot more

00:35:18.000 --> 00:35:19.630
complex than just
an empty gut that

00:35:19.630 --> 00:35:21.200
needs to be filled with wind.

00:35:21.200 --> 00:35:25.080
And so these are gradually
rejected as aphrodisiacs.

00:35:25.080 --> 00:35:29.880
And Theophile Bonet argues
that "it's commonly reported

00:35:29.880 --> 00:35:33.440
of aphrodisiacs that flatus, or
wind, is necessary for venery.

00:35:33.440 --> 00:35:36.160
But though in boys, erection
or distention of the penis may

00:35:36.160 --> 00:35:40.020
seem to be from flatus, and
these may concur by accident,

00:35:40.020 --> 00:35:42.340
yet they cannot nor ought
not to be reckoned amongst

00:35:42.340 --> 00:35:43.570
aphrodisiacs.

00:35:43.570 --> 00:35:45.650
Those things indeed
excite the spirits

00:35:45.650 --> 00:35:48.200
and stir up venery and
make the seed turgid

00:35:48.200 --> 00:35:52.520
but so do not those
things that breed wind."

00:35:52.520 --> 00:35:54.145
I think it's shame
just because they're

00:35:54.145 --> 00:35:55.380
the most fun to talk about.

00:35:55.380 --> 00:35:58.220
So it would have been nice had
they carried on a bit longer.

00:35:58.220 --> 00:36:00.450
So all of these
groups of aphrodisiacs

00:36:00.450 --> 00:36:02.810
provide the body with
something that it's missing.

00:36:02.810 --> 00:36:04.690
If your body is
cold, you heat it up.

00:36:04.690 --> 00:36:08.050
If your body lacks wind, you
eat things that give more wind.

00:36:08.050 --> 00:36:10.370
And this is in the
humor model tends

00:36:10.370 --> 00:36:12.260
to be called "curing
by contraries."

00:36:12.260 --> 00:36:14.270
So you give something
of the opposite quality

00:36:14.270 --> 00:36:16.940
to the disorder, and
it will help cure it.

00:36:16.940 --> 00:36:18.690
But there's one
group of aphrodisiacs

00:36:18.690 --> 00:36:20.550
that function under
another model,

00:36:20.550 --> 00:36:23.752
and this model is often
curing through sympathy

00:36:23.752 --> 00:36:25.960
and is sometimes called "the
doctrine of signatures."

00:36:25.960 --> 00:36:28.680
Has anyone hear
that term before?

00:36:28.680 --> 00:36:31.280
So the doctrine of
signatures basically

00:36:31.280 --> 00:36:33.210
outlines that you
can identify what

00:36:33.210 --> 00:36:36.030
something is good for by
the signature it bears.

00:36:36.030 --> 00:36:37.630
So what does it look like?

00:36:37.630 --> 00:36:39.460
And what is it similar to?

00:36:39.460 --> 00:36:42.900
And the most famous-- I'll
leave you with that picture

00:36:42.900 --> 00:36:45.630
while you think
about that phrase.

00:36:45.630 --> 00:36:49.040
So under the doctrine
of signatures,

00:36:49.040 --> 00:36:52.550
anything plant-based
that's of a phallic shape

00:36:52.550 --> 00:36:56.310
is going to work for
an aphrodisiac process

00:36:56.310 --> 00:36:58.270
and to help conception.

00:36:58.270 --> 00:37:00.310
And this plant, you can
see on the board here,

00:37:00.310 --> 00:37:02.130
is called satyrion.

00:37:02.130 --> 00:37:04.020
It's also called dogstones.

00:37:04.020 --> 00:37:05.085
It's a type of orchid.

00:37:05.085 --> 00:37:06.460
And there's a
whole set them that

00:37:06.460 --> 00:37:09.484
are called foolstones,
foxstones, dogstones.

00:37:09.484 --> 00:37:11.150
And if you remember
I mentioned earlier,

00:37:11.150 --> 00:37:13.660
stones is their
word for testicles.

00:37:13.660 --> 00:37:16.795
And so this plant is
famous in the 17th century

00:37:16.795 --> 00:37:18.370
for being an aphrodisiac.

00:37:18.370 --> 00:37:21.600
It's got a tool, fleshy, erect
stem, as they describe it,

00:37:21.600 --> 00:37:24.360
a nice bulbous head on the top,
and two bulbous little balls

00:37:24.360 --> 00:37:27.070
at the bottom covered in
roots that look like hairs.

00:37:27.070 --> 00:37:29.850
So its signature was very clear.

00:37:29.850 --> 00:37:32.330
And Richard Bunworth,
who is a commentator

00:37:32.330 --> 00:37:34.230
on the doctrine of
signatures, argues

00:37:34.230 --> 00:37:36.660
that "the roots of
satyrion, or dogstones,

00:37:36.660 --> 00:37:39.210
represent the
testicles in figure

00:37:39.210 --> 00:37:41.240
and are famous for their
[INAUDIBLE] stimulation

00:37:41.240 --> 00:37:42.670
to venery.

00:37:42.670 --> 00:37:46.354
While Oswald Croll, a writer
on chemistry and medicine,

00:37:46.354 --> 00:37:48.270
also talking about the
doctrine of signatures,

00:37:48.270 --> 00:37:51.330
stated that this was so potent
that it worked even if you just

00:37:51.330 --> 00:37:52.860
held it in your hand.

00:37:52.860 --> 00:37:54.615
You didn't even have
to consume this one.

00:37:54.615 --> 00:37:56.010
It's that good.

00:37:56.010 --> 00:37:58.480
So I think we can
all see why that

00:37:58.480 --> 00:38:00.290
functions under the
doctrine of signatures.

00:38:00.290 --> 00:38:01.789
It's quite clear
what it looks like.

00:38:01.789 --> 00:38:04.938
But there are also some
more add and unusual ones.

00:38:04.938 --> 00:38:09.410
Beans-- now, to me, beans
don't look particularly

00:38:09.410 --> 00:38:12.040
like any part of the
reproductive organs.

00:38:12.040 --> 00:38:14.680
But for people in the
17th and 18th century,

00:38:14.680 --> 00:38:16.310
they look like the
glans of the penis,

00:38:16.310 --> 00:38:19.230
so the very end of the penis,
and that's why they work.

00:38:19.230 --> 00:38:21.730
So William Salmon, who wrote
a book called "Botanologia"

00:38:21.730 --> 00:38:25.990
in 1710, informed his readers
that "a strong broth of beans

00:38:25.990 --> 00:38:28.130
stirred up lust and
was good for impotency

00:38:28.130 --> 00:38:30.290
in the male kind who
have not the power

00:38:30.290 --> 00:38:32.770
to use the act of generation,
both because they're

00:38:32.770 --> 00:38:34.340
nutritious," and
we've seen already

00:38:34.340 --> 00:38:37.570
they're windy, but, quote, "by
reason, the bean, especially

00:38:37.570 --> 00:38:39.420
the field kind,
has the signature

00:38:39.420 --> 00:38:40.980
of the glans of the penis.

00:38:40.980 --> 00:38:43.100
And for that reason,
Pythagoras and his followers

00:38:43.100 --> 00:38:46.850
judge them to be
provokers of lust."

00:38:46.850 --> 00:38:48.940
What I think is really
interesting is outside

00:38:48.940 --> 00:38:51.065
of these ones that resemble
the glans of the penis,

00:38:51.065 --> 00:38:53.250
most aphrodisiacs
by signature relate

00:38:53.250 --> 00:38:55.394
to looking like the testicles.

00:38:55.394 --> 00:38:57.810
And I think again here, you
can see the really close link.

00:38:57.810 --> 00:38:59.700
This isn't just about sex.

00:38:59.700 --> 00:39:01.590
Because if you're
augmenting the testicles,

00:39:01.590 --> 00:39:03.720
you're augmenting the
thing that produces seed,

00:39:03.720 --> 00:39:05.800
and seed is fundamental
for conception.

00:39:05.800 --> 00:39:07.730
So even when it looks
like they're just

00:39:07.730 --> 00:39:10.590
talking about sex and
sexual pleasure and desire,

00:39:10.590 --> 00:39:14.420
they're still talking about
conception and reproduction.

00:39:14.420 --> 00:39:16.845
Now, it wasn't just
plants you could

00:39:16.845 --> 00:39:19.890
eat under the doctrine
of signatures.

00:39:19.890 --> 00:39:21.670
Apologies-- this
is slightly gross.

00:39:21.670 --> 00:39:25.860
Animal genitalia were a popular
aphrodisiac at this time.

00:39:25.860 --> 00:39:30.200
The testicles and the pizzle, or
penis, of bulls, boars, goats,

00:39:30.200 --> 00:39:32.610
and stags were all recommended.

00:39:32.610 --> 00:39:35.070
Goats were often described
as a lascivious goat,

00:39:35.070 --> 00:39:36.730
even in medical texts.

00:39:36.730 --> 00:39:39.190
They say take the stones
of a lascivious goat.

00:39:39.190 --> 00:39:41.770
According to the Oxford
English Dictionary,

00:39:41.770 --> 00:39:44.762
a lecherous goat is still
a phrase and used now.

00:39:44.762 --> 00:39:46.970
I haven't heard it any time
recently, but apparently.

00:39:46.970 --> 00:39:51.550
So you can all call people
lecherous goats if you need to.

00:39:51.550 --> 00:39:53.580
While I think stags,
bulls, and boars were all

00:39:53.580 --> 00:39:55.860
a bit more obvious,
they're all seen

00:39:55.860 --> 00:39:59.030
as quite potent, quite virile
animals, particularly stags--

00:39:59.030 --> 00:40:02.650
and stag horns as
well also work--

00:40:02.650 --> 00:40:04.070
perhaps a bit more
unusually, you

00:40:04.070 --> 00:40:06.070
could also eat the brains
of these creatures.

00:40:06.070 --> 00:40:08.936
So creatures thought to be
particularly lascivious,

00:40:08.936 --> 00:40:10.810
you consume their brains,
and it will provoke

00:40:10.810 --> 00:40:13.320
you to think in the same way.

00:40:13.320 --> 00:40:16.790
So Nicholas Culpepper wrote
that "whatsoever any creature

00:40:16.790 --> 00:40:19.630
is addicted extremely to, they
move the man that eats them

00:40:19.630 --> 00:40:20.350
to the like.

00:40:20.350 --> 00:40:24.300
Therefore, partridges,
quails, sparrows, et cetera,

00:40:24.300 --> 00:40:26.490
being exceedingly
addicted to venery,

00:40:26.490 --> 00:40:29.970
they work the same in those
men and women who eat them.

00:40:29.970 --> 00:40:33.220
Now, I kind of expected
rabbits to make an appearance

00:40:33.220 --> 00:40:35.570
in this category,
given their reputation.

00:40:35.570 --> 00:40:38.910
And sometimes they'll recommend
the womb of a hare for women

00:40:38.910 --> 00:40:41.100
to eat for conception
purposes, but very

00:40:41.100 --> 00:40:43.280
rarely for aphrodisiacs.

00:40:43.280 --> 00:40:46.110
So it's very rarely connected
to the kind of desire,

00:40:46.110 --> 00:40:48.150
pleasure side of things.

00:40:48.150 --> 00:40:50.670
So poor rabbits clearly
developed their reputation

00:40:50.670 --> 00:40:53.480
slightly later than this.

00:40:53.480 --> 00:40:56.460
So those are the main types of
aphrodisiac that were in use

00:40:56.460 --> 00:40:59.920
or were being discussed by
medical writers at this time.

00:40:59.920 --> 00:41:02.700
And hopefully what you can
see is there's an awful lot

00:41:02.700 --> 00:41:03.880
to choose from.

00:41:03.880 --> 00:41:06.260
And within that, there's
a whole range of things

00:41:06.260 --> 00:41:08.930
that you could grow in the
garden, so carrots and parsnips

00:41:08.930 --> 00:41:11.330
and onions, things you
could get in hedge rows,

00:41:11.330 --> 00:41:13.620
like nettles, right the
way through to things

00:41:13.620 --> 00:41:16.280
that are more expensive,
like cinnamon and saffron.

00:41:16.280 --> 00:41:18.650
So they're really making
sure they cater to everybody

00:41:18.650 --> 00:41:21.515
and all social classes.

00:41:21.515 --> 00:41:23.140
But you might be
sitting here thinking,

00:41:23.140 --> 00:41:25.348
this is all well and good,
but they're medical texts.

00:41:25.348 --> 00:41:27.360
They're supposed to
talk about diseases.

00:41:27.360 --> 00:41:30.310
And did people outside
of those circles

00:41:30.310 --> 00:41:33.120
really think in
these kinds of ways?

00:41:33.120 --> 00:41:35.670
So I want to kind
of try and prove

00:41:35.670 --> 00:41:37.570
to you that it's a
widespread understanding,

00:41:37.570 --> 00:41:42.140
and it's not just sad medical
men writing in their books that

00:41:42.140 --> 00:41:43.810
thought this way.

00:41:43.810 --> 00:41:47.680
And early modern England is
quite consistently recognized

00:41:47.680 --> 00:41:49.430
as an era where
people are expected

00:41:49.430 --> 00:41:52.070
to know about their bodies,
to know about their health.

00:41:52.070 --> 00:41:55.150
That's a nice little Latin
phrase, nosce te ipsum,

00:41:55.150 --> 00:41:59.155
know thyself, which underpins
the idea that you should really

00:41:59.155 --> 00:42:02.660
understand your body, understand
how to keep it healthy.

00:42:02.660 --> 00:42:04.596
Physicians are also
really expensive,

00:42:04.596 --> 00:42:07.220
so it's in your best interest to
know how to cure your own body

00:42:07.220 --> 00:42:08.640
and how to help it.

00:42:08.640 --> 00:42:13.220
And we can see, therefore, that
people know the humoral model

00:42:13.220 --> 00:42:15.870
quite well and they know
their medicine quite well.

00:42:15.870 --> 00:42:17.297
And we see it in
both directions.

00:42:17.297 --> 00:42:19.130
So it's not just that
everyday people listen

00:42:19.130 --> 00:42:20.670
to what medical writers say.

00:42:20.670 --> 00:42:24.549
Medical writers also pick up
top tips from everyday people

00:42:24.549 --> 00:42:25.840
and record them in their books.

00:42:25.840 --> 00:42:27.850
So occasionally you'll
see them saying, oh,

00:42:27.850 --> 00:42:29.695
whoever it is down the
road is using this,

00:42:29.695 --> 00:42:31.070
and it seems to
work really well,

00:42:31.070 --> 00:42:33.290
and they incorporate
that into their own text.

00:42:33.290 --> 00:42:36.470
So it's quite a broad
medical culture.

00:42:36.470 --> 00:42:38.460
It's not too specialized.

00:42:38.460 --> 00:42:40.440
And we can see
this in particular

00:42:40.440 --> 00:42:43.330
if we turn to ballads.

00:42:43.330 --> 00:42:46.070
And ballads, unfortunately
not power ballads

00:42:46.070 --> 00:42:48.290
like the '80s, but
similar principle.

00:42:48.290 --> 00:42:51.210
Songs with a story
to them are printed

00:42:51.210 --> 00:42:53.510
throughout the 17th century.

00:42:53.510 --> 00:42:55.032
They're printed very cheaply.

00:42:55.032 --> 00:42:55.990
They do look like this.

00:42:55.990 --> 00:42:57.610
They're one side of
a sheet of paper.

00:42:57.610 --> 00:43:00.100
They're normally only a
couple of pence to buy.

00:43:00.100 --> 00:43:02.801
And one historian has estimated
that three to four million

00:43:02.801 --> 00:43:05.300
of these were printed in the
second half of the 17th century

00:43:05.300 --> 00:43:06.090
alone.

00:43:06.090 --> 00:43:10.310
And they always deal with kind
of popular themes and notions.

00:43:10.310 --> 00:43:12.650
And if we look at these
songs and these ballads,

00:43:12.650 --> 00:43:16.360
we see there's a whole
grouping that are completely

00:43:16.360 --> 00:43:20.120
obsessed with inadequate
husbands and impotent men

00:43:20.120 --> 00:43:21.690
and men whose
wives cheat on them

00:43:21.690 --> 00:43:24.290
and so make them into cuckolds.

00:43:24.290 --> 00:43:25.960
And what we see in
several of these

00:43:25.960 --> 00:43:28.580
is that the wives of these
insufficient husbands

00:43:28.580 --> 00:43:31.680
turn to aphrodisiacs in
order to try and ameliorate

00:43:31.680 --> 00:43:34.320
their plights and make
their lives a little better.

00:43:34.320 --> 00:43:36.950
So the wife who is the main
character in "The London

00:43:36.950 --> 00:43:39.520
Cuckold," printed in
the 1680s, explained

00:43:39.520 --> 00:43:42.160
that she gave her husband
a whole series of things

00:43:42.160 --> 00:43:43.760
to try and make him better.

00:43:43.760 --> 00:43:47.190
"She gave him kisses and
sack posset very good.

00:43:47.190 --> 00:43:49.810
Cordial, too, she never
misses, for they warm and heat

00:43:49.810 --> 00:43:50.600
the blood.

00:43:50.600 --> 00:43:54.030
Such things will create desire
and new kindle Cupid's fire.

00:43:54.030 --> 00:43:55.670
These things make
his kiss his wife

00:43:55.670 --> 00:43:57.500
and call her love and life."

00:43:57.500 --> 00:44:01.050
And sack posset is cream
with spices and eggs in it.

00:44:01.050 --> 00:44:05.205
And cordial is a bit like mulled
wine but thicker and with oats.

00:44:05.205 --> 00:44:09.820
It's kind of like a winey
gruel type of thing.

00:44:09.820 --> 00:44:11.870
Another ballad,
"The Woman's Brawl,"

00:44:11.870 --> 00:44:14.350
which I think is a great
title, included a section

00:44:14.350 --> 00:44:16.780
where the protagonist, Doll,
complained about her husband

00:44:16.780 --> 00:44:17.800
to a neighbor.

00:44:17.800 --> 00:44:19.170
And she said of him.

00:44:19.170 --> 00:44:21.350
"Thou unnatural clown,
thou, feeble dick,

00:44:21.350 --> 00:44:24.090
thou, as I'm an honest women
neighbor, I went like a fool

00:44:24.090 --> 00:44:26.570
and made him a cordial
with turkey eggs

00:44:26.570 --> 00:44:29.260
and afterwards a tansy with
new-laid eggs from a hen

00:44:29.260 --> 00:44:30.820
trod by gamecock.

00:44:30.820 --> 00:44:34.070
I put comfrey and clary in and
fed him lamb stones, caviar,

00:44:34.070 --> 00:44:37.390
and potato pies, yet he could
do no more good to a woman

00:44:37.390 --> 00:44:39.140
than a boy of a year old."

00:44:39.140 --> 00:44:42.099
She's not very happy
with him in this ballad.

00:44:42.099 --> 00:44:43.640
What I think is
really interesting is

00:44:43.640 --> 00:44:46.472
in medical texts, aphrodisiacs
are thought to work.

00:44:46.472 --> 00:44:47.930
And in all of these
kinds of texts,

00:44:47.930 --> 00:44:49.660
quite often they don't work.

00:44:49.660 --> 00:44:51.990
And I think predominantly,
this is because it's funnier

00:44:51.990 --> 00:44:52.930
if they don't work.

00:44:52.930 --> 00:44:54.780
And they work better
for the kind of genre

00:44:54.780 --> 00:44:58.490
if they don't succeed in
making the husband particularly

00:44:58.490 --> 00:45:01.015
lusty or fertile.

00:45:01.015 --> 00:45:03.140
But both of those ballads
I just spoke to you about

00:45:03.140 --> 00:45:05.930
